DIGEST
SB 364 Original 2026 Regular Session Barrow
Present law authorizes the Louisiana Public Service Commission to supervise, govern,
regulate, and control the transportation or sale of natural gas moving through pipeline to
local distributing systems for resale for the purposes of fixing and regulating the rates
charged and the service furnished by such public utilities.
Proposed law retains present law and further authorizes the commission to review and
evaluate rates and to fix and regulate fair and equitable rates charged for public utilities.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 45:302(A) and 1163(A)(1) and (C))
